11 AMEND PUBLIC STREET DEDICATION ABANDONMENT PROCESS
12 SECTION 1.6. G.S. 136-96 reads as rewritten:
13 "§ 136-96. Road or street not used within 15 years after dedication deemed abandoned;
14 declaration of withdrawal recorded; joint tenants or tenants in common; defunct
15 corporations.
16 (a) Every strip, piece, or parcel of land that has been at any time dedicated to public use
17 as a road, highway, street, avenue, or for any other purpose whatsoever, by a deed, grant, map,
18 plat, or other means, and that has not been actually opened and used by the public within 15 years
19 after its dedication is conclusively presumed to have been abandoned by the public for the
20 purposes for which it was dedicated; and no person shall have any right or cause of action
21 thereafter to enforce any public or private easement in the land.
22 (b) Notwithstanding subsection (a) of this section, no abandonment of any public or
23 private right or easement shall be presumed until the dedicator or a person claiming under the
24 dedicator files or causes to be recorded in the register's office of the county where the land lies a
25 declaration withdrawing the strip, piece, or parcel of land from the public or private use to which
26 it was dedicated.
27 (c) When the fee simple title is vested in tenants in common or joint tenants of any land
28 embraced within the boundaries of a road, highway, street, avenue, or other land dedicated for
29 any public purpose whatsoever, as described in this section, any one or more of the cotenants, on
30 the cotenant's behalf and on behalf of the other cotenants, may execute and cause to be registered
31 in the office of the register of deeds of the county where the land is situated the declaration of
32 withdrawal provided for in this section. Under Chapter 46A (Partition) of the General Statutes
33 and Article 29A (Judicial Sales) of Chapter 1 of the General Statutes, and on petition of any one
34 or more of the cotenants, the land thereafter may be partitioned by sale only as between or among
35 the cotenants, irrespective of who may be in actual possession of the land. In the partition
36 proceeding, any cotenant may object to the withdrawal certificate and the court shall thereupon
37 order the certificate cancelled of record.
38 (d) When any corporation has dedicated any strip, piece, or parcel of land in the manner
39 set out in this section, and the dedicating corporation is no longer in existence, the corporation is
40 conclusively presumed to have no further right, title, or interest in the land, regardless of the
41 provisions of conveyances from the corporation, or those holding under the corporation, retaining
42 title and interest in the land. The right, title, and interest in the land is conclusively presumed to
43 be vested in those persons owning lots or parcels of land adjacent to it, subject to the provisions
44 of this section.
45 (e) This section does not apply in any of the following circumstances:
46 (1) When the continued use of any strip of land dedicated for street or highway
47 purposes is necessary to afford convenient ingress or egress to any lot or parcel
48 of land sold and conveyed by the dedicator of the street or highway.
49 (2) When the public dedication is part of a future street shown on the street plan
50 adopted pursuant to G.S. 136-66.2. Upon request, a city shall adopt a
51 resolution indicating that the dedication described in the proposed declaration
House Bill 661-First Edition Page 3

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 of withdrawal is or is not part of the street plan adopted under G.S. 136-66.2.
2 This resolution shall be attached to the declaration of withdrawal and shall be
3 registered in the office of the register of deeds of the county where the land is
4 situated.
5 (f) Any strip, piece, or parcel of land that was dedicated to public use as a local road,
6 highway, street, or avenue by plat on December 22, 1978, but that has not been maintained as a
7 local public road, highway, street, or avenue by a local governmental entity by January 1, 2025,
8 is hereby deemed withdrawn for public use, any rights of the public therein are deemed
9 abandoned, and no person or governmental entity shall have any right or cause of action to
10 enforce any public interest or easement in such land pursuant to this section."
