12 PART II. NORTH CAROLINA STATE BUILDING CODE
13
14 EXEMPT MODEL HOMES FROM FIRE PROTECTION WATER SUPPLY
15 REQUIREMENT DURING CONSTRUCTION
16 SECTION 2.1.(a) Definitions. – For the purposes of this section, the following
17 definitions apply:
18 (1) Code. – The North Carolina State Building Code, and amendments to the
19 Code, as adopted by the Councils.
20 (2) Councils. – The Building Code Council and Residential Code Council.
21 (3) Model home. – As defined in G.S. 160D-1501(a).
22 (4) Water Supply Rules. – Section 3312.1, when required, of the North Carolina
23 Fire Code, and Section 3313.1, where required, of the North Carolina Building
24 Code.
25 SECTION 2.1.(b) Water Supply Rules. – Until the effective date of the rules to
26 amend Water Supply Rules, the Office of the State Fire Marshal, the Councils, and State and
27 local governments enforcing the Code shall implement Water Supply Rules as provided in
28 subsection (c) of this section.
29 SECTION 2.1.(c) Implementation. – Notwithstanding Water Supply Rules, the fire
30 code official is authorized to reduce the fire-flow requirements for an isolated model home at a
31 subdivision project site where development of full-fire flow requirements is impractical or
32 pending.
33 SECTION 2.1.(d) Additional Rulemaking Authority. – The Council shall adopt rules
34 to amend Water Supply Rules to be consistent with subsection (c) of this section.
35 Notwithstanding G.S. 150B-19(4), the rule adopted by the Council pursuant to this section shall
36 be substantively identical to the provisions of subsection (c) of this section. Rules adopted
37 pursuant to this section are not subject to Part 3 of Article 2A of Chapter 150B of the General
38 Statutes. Rules adopted pursuant to this section shall become effective as provided in
39 G.S. 150B-21.3(b1) as though 10 or more written objections had been received as provided in
40 G.S. 150B-21.3(b2).
41 SECTION 2.1.(e) Additional Residential Code Council Rulemaking Authority. –
42 The Residential Code Council shall adopt rules to amend the 2024 North Carolina State Building
43 Code volumes specified within G.S. 143-138(a)(1) through (10) to make conforming changes to
44 codes applicable to residential construction consistent with rules adopted by the Building Code
45 Council as required by subsection (d) of this section. Rules adopted pursuant to this subsection
46 are not subject to Part 3 of Article 2A of Chapter 150B of the General Statutes. Rules adopted
47 pursuant to this subsection shall become effective as provided in G.S. 150B-21.3(b1) as though
48 10 or more written objections had been received as provided in G.S. 150B-21.3(b2).
49 SECTION 2.1.(f) Sunset. – This section expires when permanent rules adopted as
50 required by subsections (d) and (e) of this section become effective.
51
