7 PART III. VARIOUS CONTRACTOR BOARDS
8
9 INCREASE CERTAIN PLUMBING AND HEATING BOARD CONTRACTOR BOARD
10 EXAMINATION AND LICENSE FEES
11 SECTION 3.1.(a) G.S. 87-22 reads as rewritten:
12 "§ 87-22. License fee; expiration and renewal; reinstatement.
13 All persons, firms, or corporations engaged in the business of either plumbing or heating
14 contracting, or both, shall pay an annual license fee not to exceed one hundred fifty dollars
15 ($150.00). three hundred dollars ($300.00). The annual fee for a piping or restricted classification
16 license shall not exceed that for a plumbing or heating license. All persons, firms, or corporations
17 engaged in the business of fire sprinkler contracting shall pay an initial application fee not to
18 exceed seventy-five dollars ($75.00) and an annual license fee not to exceed three hundred dollars
19 ($300.00). In the event the Board refuses to license an applicant, the license fee deposited shall
20 be returned by the Board to the applicant. All licenses shall expire on the last day of December
21 in each year following their issuance or renewal. Persons who obtain a license by passing an
22 examination on or after October 1 of any year may receive a license for the remainder of the year
23 by paying one-half of the usual license fee for that classification of license. It shall be the duty
24 of the secretary and treasurer to send by United States mail or e-mail to every licensee registered
25 with the Board, notice to the licensee's last known address reflected on the records of the Board
26 of the amount of fee required for renewal of license, the notice to be mailed at least one month
27 in advance of the expiration of the license. The Board may require payment of all unpaid annual
28 fees before reissuing a license. In the event of failure on the part of any person, firm or
29 corporation to renew the license certificate annually and pay the required fee during the month
30 of January in each year, the Board shall increase the license fee by twenty-five dollars ($25.00)
31 an amount not to exceed fifty dollars ($50.00) to cover any additional expense associated with
32 late renewal. The Board shall require reexamination upon failure of a licensee to renew license
33 within three years after expiration. The Board may adopt regulations requiring attendance at
34 programs of continuing education as a condition of license renewal. A licensee employed full
35 time as a local government plumbing, heating, or mechanical inspector and holding qualifications
36 from the Code Officials Qualifications Board may renew the license at a fee not to exceed
37 twenty-five dollars ($25.00)."
38 SECTION 3.1.(b) G.S. 87-22.1 reads as rewritten:
39 "§ 87-22.1. Examination fees; funds disbursed upon warrant of chairman and
40 secretary-treasurer.
41 The Board shall charge a nonrefundable application and examination fee not to exceed one
42 hundred fifty dollars ($150.00) two hundred dollars ($200.00) for each examination or any part
43 of an examination, and the funds collected shall be disbursed upon warrant of the chairman and
44 secretary-treasurer, to partially defray general expenses of the Board. The application and
45 examination fee shall be retained by the Board whether or not the applicant is granted a license.
46 Until changed by the Board pursuant to rules adopted by the Board, the fee for each examination
47 or any part taken on a particular day shall be one hundred dollars ($100.00)."
48 SECTION 3.1.(c) This section becomes effective July 1, 2025, and applies to
49 applications for examination and licensure received by the Board on or after that date.
