6 SECTION 3.4. Article 4 of Chapter 87 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
7 a new section to read:
8 "§ 87-47.1. Investigation records of the Board.
9 All records, papers, investigative files, investigative notes, reports, other investigative
10 information, and other documents containing information in the possession of or received,
11 gathered, or completed by the Board, its members, staff, employees, attorneys, or consultants as
12 a result of investigations, inquiries, assessments, or interviews conducted in connection with a
13 license application or disciplinary action initiated by the Board shall not be considered public
14 records within the meaning of Chapter 132 of the General Statutes. Documents described in this
15 section are privileged, confidential, and not subject to discovery, subpoena, or other means of
16 legal compulsion for release to any person other than the Board or its employees or consultants.
17 If any record, paper, or other document containing information collected and compiled by or on
18 behalf of the Board is received and admitted in evidence in any hearing before the Board, the
19 documents shall be a public record within the meaning of Chapter 132 of the General Statutes."
