7 "§ 87-2. Licensing Board; organization.
8 There is created the State Licensing Board for General Contractors consisting of nine
9 members appointed by the Governor for staggered five-year terms. Five of the members shall be
10 general contractors, one member shall be a registered engineer who practices structural
11 engineering, and three shall be public members. Of the general contractor members, one shall
12 have as the larger part of his the contractor's business the construction of highways; one shall
13 have as the larger part of his the contractor's business the construction of public utilities; one
14 shall have as the larger part of his the contractor's business the construction of buildings; and two
15 shall have as a larger part of their the contractor's businesses the construction of residences, one
16 of whom shall be the holder of an unlimited general contractor's license. The public members
17 shall have no ties with the construction industry and shall represent the interests of the public at
18 large. Members shall serve until the expiration of their respective terms and until their successors
19 are appointed and qualified. Vacancies occurring during a term shall be filled by appointment of
20 the Governor for the remainder of the unexpired term. The Governor may remove any member
21 of the Board for misconduct, incompetency, or neglect of duty. No Board member shall serve
22 more than two complete consecutive terms.
