42 "§ 87-15.1. Reciprocity of licensing.
43 To the extent that other states which provide for the licensing of general contractors provide
44 for similar action, the Board in its discretion may grant licenses of the same or equivalent
45 classification to general contractors licensed by other states, without written examination upon
46 satisfactory proof furnished to the Board that the qualifications of such applicants are equal to
47 the qualifications of holders of similar licenses in North Carolina and upon payment of the
48 required fee.
