36 duties on the Board in addition to the duties of their office.
37 (c) Vacancies in the Board occurring for any reason shall be filled for the unexpired term
38 by the person making the appointment.
39 "§ 143-151.10. Compensation.
40 Members of the Board who are State officers or employees shall receive no salary for serving
41 on the Board, but shall be reimbursed for their expenses in accordance with G.S. 138-6. Members
42 of the Board who are full-time salaried public officers or employees other than State officers or
43 employees shall receive no salary for serving on the Board, but shall be reimbursed for
44 subsistence and travel expenses in accordance with G.S. 138-5(a)(2) and (3). All other members
45 of the Board shall receive compensation and reimbursement for expenses in accordance with
46 G.S. 138-5(a).
