12 "§ 143-151.13. Required standards and certificates for Code-enforcement
13 officials.certificates.
14 (a) No person shall engage in Code enforcement under this Article unless that person
15 possesses one of the following types of certificates, currently valid, issued by the Board attesting
16 to that person's qualifications to engage in Code enforcement: (i) a standard certificate; (ii) a
17 limited certificate provided for in subsection (c) of this section; or (iii) a probationary certificate
18 provided for in subsection (d) of this section. To obtain a standard certificate, a person must pass
19 an examination, as prescribed by the Board or by a contracting party under G.S. 143-151.16(d),
20 that is based on the North Carolina State Building Code and administrative procedures required
21 for Code enforcement. The Board may issue a standard certificate of qualification to each person
22 who successfully completes the examination. The certificate authorizes that person to engage in
23 the practice of Code enforcement and to practice as a qualified Code-enforcement official in
24 North Carolina. The certificate of qualification shall bear the signatures of the chairman chair
25 and secretary of the Board.
26 (b) The Board shall issue one or more standard certificates to each person seeking to
27 practice Code enforcement as a certified Code-enforcement official by demonstrating the
28 qualifications set forth in subsection (b1) (b2) of this section. Standard certificates are available
29 for each of the following types of qualified for Code-enforcement officials:
30 (1) Building inspector.
31 (2) Electrical inspector.
32 (3) Mechanical inspector.
33 (4) Plumbing inspector.
34 (5) Fire inspector.
35 (6) Residential changeout inspector.
