38 official issued pursuant to the provisions of this Article must be renewed annually on or before
39 the first day of July. Each application for renewal must be accompanied by a renewal fee to be
40 determined by the Board, but not to exceed ten dollars ($10.00). The Board is authorized to
41 charge an extra four dollar ($4.00) late renewal fee for renewals made after the first day of July
42 each year.
43 (c) Any person who fails to renew his the certificate for a period of two consecutive years
44 may be required by the Board to take and pass the same examination as unlicensed applicants
45 before allowing such person to renew his the certificate.
46 (d) The Board may contract with persons for the development and administration of the
47 examinations required by G.S. 143-151.13(a), for course development related to the
48 examinations, for review of a particular applicant's examination, and for other related services.
